postcontent: I have a very good condition Hungarian AMD-65 side folder in 7.62x39. This is not the widely available version with a cheap US barrel; it is the much harder to find TGI SA2000 FEG with original chrome-lined FEG barrel. It is more true to the original in that the barrel is the correct length, and it has an extended AMD style muzzle break spot-welded on. These are difficult to find and relatively expensive when you do as they are no longer made. This original 12.5" barrel is easy to convert to an SBR if you get a tax stamp and are inclined to do so. This specific example has the "AMD65 Tech" cheek-weld adapter installed, as well as an aluminum quad rail and a hogue pistol grip. It does also include the original furniture to convert it back to it's normal configuration. It is in very good condition with some minor finish wear on some of the corners as is to be expected if you are familiar with this variant. It shoots and functions perfectly and has been well maintained. If you aren't familiar with it, do a little Google-fu; it's a great rifle. More photos available on request for serious inquiries. title: For Sale/Trade:  Arsenal
postcontent: Arsenal SLR-95 in 7.62x39. Originally came with thumbhole stock. Receiver is milled, and SLR-95s are known to be a highly sought after accurate AKM pattern rifle. Gun has between 6-800 rounds through it, and bore is clean. Only permanent modification is a hole drilled through the reciever to accomodate a Magpul Zhukov stock which has been itself modified in order to accept the milled top tang that is still in factory position/condition. Milled receivers are at a different angle than stamped recievers, so while the stock is affixed permanently via a bolt into the receiver as well as the attachment to the tang, there was a small gap where you could see between the receiver and stock. There is a thin layer of epoxy that fills this gap and is used only to do so. All work has been completed by a gunsmith who works on AK pattern rifles. It is possible to reinstall the old stock which I will include, or to make other arrangments for a conversion to a stock using an ACE block or Ironwood designs stock. There is an attached Hogue grip, and bulgarian polymer forearm, as well as a bulgarian sling. Rattlecan paint job.

title: For Sale:  P38 SVW/45 Rare Mauser - SOLD
postcontent: The Mauser manufactured P38s were initially stamped "byf" until around late 1944 or early 1945 when the "byf" manufacturing code was changed to "SVW" for the last few months of the war.The left side of this P38 has the stacked SVW manufacturer designation over the year code of 45 (SVW/45). The right side of this 1945 P38 has the eagle over the WaA135 Inspection/Acceptance (E/WaA135) mark flanking both sides of the military test fire proof mark, the eagle over the swastika in the center.This is a great opportunity to own a highly desirable and collectable P38 with a low s/n of "547 f" that dates this P38 to just before the war ended.  It is not an Interarms import or a Russian capture and there are no French star stamps. It is an rare authentic late war German military issue 1945 SVW P38 with all matching serial numbers on the frame, slide, under barrel, and locking block. Out of approximately 1.2 million P38s, only a small number (3000 or less) were "f" block SVW P38s - the last block of Mauser manufactured P38s. This "f" block was fully functioning when placed in storage over 30+ years ago, and appears in every way to be in very good condition. Please refer to the photo and request additional information if interested.  Very competitively priced at $1750.  Local pickup or buyer pays shipping.
